---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy | Stimmie's Guides"
  description="How Stimmie's Guides handles visitor data, analytics, and third-party services."
>
  <main class="legal-page">
    <a href="/" class="back-link">&larr; All guides</a>

    <header class="legal-header">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="legal-lede">
        Last updated: July 4, 2026. Stimmie's Guides is a personal student-resource site
        operated by Stimmie. It is <strong>not</strong> an official University of the
        Philippines Los Baños (UPLB) website.
      </p>
    </header>

    <article class="legal-body">
      <section>
        <h2>What this site is</h2>
        <p>
          This site hosts free guides and handbooks for students. There are no user
          accounts, logins, or comment forms. You can read everything without signing up.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Information we may process</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Visitor counter.</strong> A lightweight counter (via abacus.jasoncameron.dev)
            records aggregate page visits per guide. Your browser may store a local date stamp
            so repeat views on the same day are not double-counted.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Analytics.</strong> The site may use Vercel Web Analytics to understand
            traffic patterns (page views, referrers). We do not intentionally collect your
            name or student number through analytics.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Hosting logs.</strong> Vercel and our hosting providers may log standard
            request metadata (IP address, user agent, timestamps) for security and reliability.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>What we do not do</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>We do not sell personal data.</li>
          <li>We do not require accounts or collect passwords on this site.</li>
          <li>We do not run advertising trackers beyond basic hosting/analytics noted above.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Third-party links</h2>
        <p>
          Guides may link to external sites (campus systems, tools, social pages). Those
          services have their own privacy policies.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Questions about this policy? Reach out via
          <a href="https://stimmie.dev" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">stimmie.dev</a>.
        </p>
      </section>
    </article>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  .legal-page {
    max-width: 42rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 2rem 1rem 4rem;
  }

  .back-link {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: #6b7280;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .back-link:hover {
    color: #111;
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .legal-header {
    margin: 1.5rem 0 2rem;
  }

  .legal-header h1 {
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
  }

  .legal-lede {
    color: #4b5563;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .legal-body section {
    margin-bottom: 1.75rem;
  }

  .legal-body h2 {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
  }

  .legal-body p,
  .legal-body li {
    color: #4b5563;
    line-height: 1.65;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .legal-body ul {
    margin: 0.5rem 0 0;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
  }

  .legal-body a {
    color: inherit;
  }
</style>
